      "writtenOn": "2026-07-15T06:19:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Question: checkThresholds() looks like it runs on every poll (updateValue() → checkThresholds(), with restartRead() rescheduling), not only at boot. If so, value \u003e 0 skips all zero readings at any time — would a fan that genuinely stalls during normal operation (0 RPM) then no longer raise a threshold alarm or update redundancy? I\u0027d like to understand how a boot-transient 0 is distinguished from a real 0-RPM stall. As one option, a startup settle window / marking the sensor non-functional until the first valid reading / requiring N consecutive zeros might filter boot-time false alarms without affecting real failure detection — just a thought.",
      "revId": "6964af47cd5bb02acd36f27b19ffeabc2fe84bd7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e93223fd_82c3d287",
